As a senior consumer insights strategist focusing on the Gujarat luxury real estate market, I have synthesized current market signals regarding Ahmedabad’s "Ultra-Luxury" segment (specifically Sindhu Bhavan Road, Ambli, and parts of Prahlad Nagar). 

The buyer in this segment is typically a "New-Money" industrialist or a high-growth service sector professional (CXO/Partner level) who views Ahmedabad not as a secondary city, but as an emerging global business hub. Unlike Mumbai/Delhi, Ahmedabad's luxury buyers are deeply rooted in the "Gujarati Business Family" structure; even high-net-worth individuals defer to multi-generational input.

Here is the structured persona based on observed market behavior:

```json
{
  "age_range": "38–52 years",
  "net_worth": "₹25 Cr – ₹75 Cr (Liquid Assets + Business Valuation)",
  "primary_motivation": "Lifestyle Upgradation & Social Signaling (Establishing residence in the 'Power Corridor' of SBR/Ambli is considered a badge of success among the city's influential business circles).",
